-- Hyundai Heavy, Japan Tobacco, State Bank: Asia Stocks Preview
-- B y   K a n a   N i s h i z a w a
-- 2012-06-15T11:31:13Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-15/hyundai-heavy-japan-tobacco-state-bank-asia-stocks-preview.html
The following companies may have
unusual price changes in Asian trading on June 18.  Stock symbols are in parentheses and share  prices  are as of
the latest close. The information in each item was released
after markets shut unless stated otherwise.  Hyundai Heavy Industries Co. (009540)  (009540 KS): The South Korean
shipbuilder’s January-May orders fell 53 percent from a year
earlier to $7.3 billion, according to a regulatory filing. The
stock was unchanged at 272,500 won.  Japan Tobacco Inc. (2914)  (2914 JT): The company’s domestic
cigarette sales climbed 43.6 percent in May, according to a
statement to the Tokyo Stock Exchange. The stock lost 0.8
percent to 446,500 yen.  State Bank of India Ltd.  (SBIN IN):  India ’s biggest lender
cut  interest rates  on loans to some sectors by 50 basis points
to 350 basis points, managing director Krishna Kumar said in
Mumbai today. The lender expects its loan book to grow at a
faster pace after the cuts, Kumar said. The shares advanced 1.5
percent to 2,183.1 rupees.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kana Nishizawa in  Hong Kong  at 
